<h1>GNOME 2.4 Desktop &amp; Developer Platform</h1>

<p>The GNOME 2.4 Desktop and Platform release is the latest version of the
popular, multi-platform free desktop environment.</p>

<p>GNOME runs on a variety of platforms, including GNU/Linux (commonly called
Linux), Solaris, HP-UX, BSD and Apple's Darwin.  GNOME includes powerful
features such as high-quality smooth text rendering and first class
internationalization and accessibility support, including support for
bi-directional text.</p>

<p>GNOME is part of <a href="http://www.gnu.org/">The GNU Project</a>, and is
<a href="http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html">Free Software</a>.</p>

<p>Please read release notes for detailed installation instructions and
information on this release.</p>
